The paper focuses on caching and delivery techniques in wireless radio access networks, which are primarily related to networking and communication (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses interference management, which is a common topic in signal processing (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes new delivery schemes that leverage caching, which can be considered as a form of content-based recommendation or personalized content delivery, falling under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
